Miss South Africa Adè van Heerden sustained minor injuries following a car accident in Randpark Ridge, Johannesburg. Her organisation took to Twitter to confirm the incident. The Miss South Africa Organization confirms that Adè van Heerden was involved in a car accident on Sunday afternoon.
We are relieved to report that despite minor bumps and bruises, Adè is well.
We thank everyone for respecting her privacy while she recovers. — Miss South Africa (@Official_MissSA) March 12, 2018 The organisation thanked everyone for respecting the beauty queen’s privacy while she recovers. It is reported that at the time of the accident, Adè was driving a Nissan X Trail which she received as part of her prize package after being crowned Miss South Africa. -TNA Reporter 